Text.string: You've gotta help Dr. Ace!

There's a doctor named Ace Baron who needs your help. He lost his staff! Head to the Mt. Schuler Recovery Center and do the thing! Then we'll BOTH be showered with praise and admiration for our good deeds!
The Maliwan Medical Corps stole a bunch of my supplies. They will DEFINITELY try to kill you when you take 'em back, straight up. So kill them first, word? Word.
Hell yeah! Stick it to those Maliwan suckaaas! Haha, that was old school! Fresh.
Okay, screw it, I'll donate some of my own. Grab this empty hemo-pack and give me an assist.
Ohhhh, shit!
Oh—guh! Sorry! Sorry! Sorry!
I... apologize.
Sorry! Oh, uh, I didn't mean—oh, sorry!
Some bandits jacked a bunch of my medical supplies! Find them and blast their janky ride!
Oh, snap! They're getting away! After 'em!
Yes! That was gangster AF! Now grab those supplies and get out of there.
Niiiiiiice.
Nah, you gotta blast that thing! The supplies are locked in the trunk!
We need hexapriazine, skag oil, Melodinax, and hemo-packs. Track some down for me, will ya?
Yo, that's all the medicine. We still need another hemo-pack, but we'll figure it out. Come on back, playa.
Looks like we're still a little short on hemoglobin. “Hemoglobin Disrobin'” is the title track on my mixtape, by the way. Did you want one or...? No? Still no?
Okay, now... very, very carefully.
Just delicately use the hemo-pack on my arm, okay?
Breathe. We'll get through this. Just use the hemo-pack.
Use the hemo-pack and tap me up already!
Okay. Easy does it. Easy now.
Ohhhghghgh! Yep. Okay. That'll do.
Okay, um... thanks, I think. At least, maybe this'll finally give me some street cred. Ugh. Maybe I'll get one of those... sweet Atlas robot arms...

Hey, recruit! Seven years ago, I started the “Clapslist” service to connect people in need with heroes like you! I... look, I forgot the password. But hey, these requests are ONLY seven years old, so I bet these people still need help/are alive!
Are you listening, fool? You gotta blow that thing up!
Blow up the ride and get the sweet supplies, yo!
Gotta blast that thing, not ride in it!
I told you, straight up, you gotta wreck that truck!
Got another old Clapslist mission for you, recruit!

There's a doctor on Promethea named Ace Baron who needs your help. He lost his staff! Head to the Mt. Schuler Recovery Center and do the thing! Then we'll BOTH be showered with praise and admiration for our good deeds!
A Vault Hunter? What are YOU doin' up in here?
Claptrap said something about a lost staff at Mt. Schuler?
Claptrap said something about lost staff?
The small robot said it was about your lost staff.
Somethin' about lost staff, boyo. Ring a bell?

Seriously? I put that request up, like, seven years ago! Back when I had a respectable establishment, not this crap pile you see now. But I AM glad you're here. See, I'm tryin' to help out all the poor bastards affected by this war, but yo, straight up, we are running short on med supplies.
Bee-tee-dubs, I'm not just a doctor of medicine. My practice is in combat trauma, but my residency was in rhyme. Word.
That punk-ass is a black market dealer. I'll bet dollars to deez-nuts he stole those supplies. Dude's a pushover though. Just threaten him and he'll give 'em up.
Oh, snap! I forgot to give you a mixtape! D'you want one?
Yeah, yeah, yeah, no, I get it. You're concentratin' on your flow. I'll hit you with it later.
Solid, VH. Feelin' inspired by your work! Much love.
Aw, dip, the pharmacy! Been abandoned for a while, but there should be some supplies left. Heard this place was infested, though. Squash those ratchet-ass ratches.
And you KNOW that ain't sanitary, but my patients need their meds. Straight up.
Yeah, yeah. We've all got a sob story. As for me, I've got patients to heal and no patience to deal! Just threaten him and be done with it.

I got some supplies here, and I'm happy to sell them for a reasonably marked-up price. I'm just trying to feed my family. You understand, right? Please, don't shoot. There's been enough bloodshed around here. Just gimme the cash and we can make a deal.
You don't know what's like down here. People don't eat for days. It's a nightmare.
Look, I'm happy to sell these supplies to you, okay? Just put the money on the table and we'll call it a deal.
You give me the cash, I give you the supplies. Easy.
Easy, easy. No need for violence, just cash on the table.
Just tryna do business. No need to get violent.
Fine. But you're lucky I'm in a good mood.
I'll help you. But you'd better think about your life choices, you hear me?
I will overlook your transgression so you may feed your pack.
I'm in a giving mood. It's rare, but it happens. Lucky you!
Wow, thank you so much! You have no idea how much this means to me and my family!
Man. Get your punk-ass outta here before my Vault Hunter changes their mind.
Well, that's not quite enough cash, but... I'll take it. Thank you! You have no idea how much this means to me and my family.
Give me those supplies or kiss your kneecaps goodbye.
How about this? You give me back the supplies you stole, and I DON'T implode your face. Deal?
If you don't give up the supplies, I will be forced to intimidate you. Would you like to see that?
Listen, boyo. You're gonna give me back those supplies, or I'm gonna break things. Lots of things. On you.
Whoa, whoa! Okay, fine! Take 'em, they're yours! Just please, don't hurt me!
That's what I'm talking about! You had that fool straight up fear-dumping!
I know what you're thinkin'. “What's this doctor doing tryna be a rapper?” But listen. Medicine, it comes and goes. But my rhymes? That's healin' for the soul.
Look, just... let me spit something for you. “See, I bust raps like I bust caps, and that's that. Don't mess with my knapsacks full of fat stacks or else you get the clap backs!” Word? Word.
Okay, screw it, I'll donate some of my own. Go grab that empty hemo-pack and give me an assist over here.
But hey, don't worry about me, I'll survive. And so will my patients, thanks to you. Mt. Schuler is finally ready to staff up and heal the hurt!
Ura, please. I'm from Partali. I don't want your weak-ass rhymes.
No.
Oh, I don't... um... listen to music? Yeah.
Oh, ah. Well. Maybe later, boyo.
Oh, by the way. That Hardin guy stopped by. Wanted you to have this—his way of saying thanks, I guess. Word.
Last chance on that mixtape, by the way.||Still no? Word? Word.
Sorry, friend, but that's not enough cash. I can't sell these supplies for just that. Get some more money, or I walk away from the deal.
